project.description:
Manually created clone of openstack-mkcloud for testing the new log-parser plugin
https://wiki.jenkins-ci.org/display/JENKINS/Log+Parser+Plugin

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: cloudsource
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Can be something like develcloud6 (uses Devel:Cloud:*, see TESTHEAD parameter for Staging), susecloud6 (uses SUSE:*), GM3 (uses the GM ISO)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: mkcloudtarget
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Set mkcloudtarget to define the mkcloud command line parameters.

hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.name: storage_method
hudson.model.ChoiceParameterDefinition.description: Select storage method: default (let mkcloud decide), none (enforce none)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: github_pr
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: String is a ':' separated list of these vaules: $ORG/$repo:$PR_ID:$SHA1:$BRANCH:$context Note: SHA1 must be latest commit in PR, $context is optional (only use if multiple gating runs needed per PR)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: job_name
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: This name will become the build name of the job. It will appear in the list of builds (webUI, RSS feed).

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: UPDATEBEFOREINSTALL
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: add update repos before crowbar install

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: TESTHEAD
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: if non-empty, test latest version from Devel:Cloud (:1.0)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: nodenumber
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: number of nodes excl. admin-node minimum 2=controller+compute

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: nodenumbercompute
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Number of compute nodes

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_tempest
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: can be used for force off(0) or on(1)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: tempestoptions
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Additional options to pass to the "run_tempest.sh -N " step. Use just \"-t\" for a full tempest run.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: ostestroptions
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: If given, a extra ostestr run is executed (after the default tempest run). Use i.e. " --regex '^magnum.tests.functional.api'"

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_horizon_integration_test
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Execute selenium integration tests for Horizon after Tempest. This test is in beta, and a fail will not be considered for now.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_sles12
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Set to 1 if sle12 nodes should be installed

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_sles12sp2
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: deploy cloud7 with SP2 instead of SP1

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: upgrade_cloudsource
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: In case of using upgrade, upgrade to that cloudsource version

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: hacloud
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: If hacloud=1 then deploy a 4-node cluster

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: WITHCROWBARREGISTER
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: boot up one lonely node in the admin network and register it with crowbar_register (image type depends on want_sles12 parameter)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_all_ssl
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to 1 to deploy all cloud services with SSL aka HTTPS

hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.name: want_cindermultibackend
hudson.model.BooleanParameterDefinition.description: enables deployment of more than one cinder backend

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: cinder_netapp_login
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: the password for the user "openstack" as configured on the netapp server

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: cinder_netapp_password
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: the password for the user "openstack" as configured on the netapp server

org.jvnet.jenkins.plugins.nodelabelparam.name: label
org.jvnet.jenkins.plugins.nodelabelparam.description: Default: openstack-mkcloud | Possible values: openstack-mkcloud-SLE11 (SLE11 host) | openstack-mkcloud-SLE12 (SLE12 host) | openstack-mkcloud-SLE12-aarch64 (SLE12 aarch64 host)

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_node_aliases
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: List of aliases to assign to nodes. Takes all provided aliases and assign them to available nodes successively. Examples want_node_aliases='controller=1,ceph=2,compute=1' assigns the aliases to 4 nodes as controller, ceph1, ceph2, compute want_node_aliases='data=1,services=2,storage=2' assigns the aliases to 5 nodes as data, service1, service2, storage1, storage2

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: scenario
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Defines which scenario file should be used. Only works with cloud5 or newer. Currently only the 'batch' step uses such a file.

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_docker
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to 1 to deploy with docker

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_test_updates
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: allow disabling of test updates

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_magnum
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Deploy with Magnum

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_barbican
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Deploy with Barbican

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: vcpus
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: number of vcpus for the compute nodes

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_sahara
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to 1 to deploy sahara

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_rootfs
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to btrfs to deploy with btrfs

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_postgresql
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to 1 to deploy with postgresql

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_efi
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: Set to UEFI boot admin node

hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.name: want_murano
hudson.model.StringParameterDefinition.description: set to 1 to deploy murano

hudson.model.TextParameterDefinition.name: custom_settings
hudson.model.TextParameterDefinition.description: This holds shell code and will be executed before calling mkcloud. This should not be used by default or regularly. It is meant to test PRs with special configurations.
